 Is working for a company on cutting-edge cyber security, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Big Data Analytics seem exciting to you? Do you want to work at a company where you can make a huge difference? If you are someone that wants to grow and learn new things, while helping to contribute to the development/enhancement of our provisioning and operations processes and broaden your expertise with information technology and cyber security project planning in a fast-paced environment, then you may be the perfect candidate! 
 You will be a key contributor as this is a customer-facing role that entails working with all levels of external customers and a variety of cross-functional internal team members. You will also have many opportunities to grow your knowledge and hone your technical skills as you work on projects that include the implementation of cutting-edge technology. The Project Coordinator role includes conducting Service Reviews and portal training with customers on SODs products and services. The Project Coordinator will act as a liaison between SOD and the client. You will be the voice of the customer to advocate on their behalf. 
 Security On-Demand (SOD) is the leading innovator in the industry for threat Management, Detection, and Response (MDR). Founded in 2001, Security On-Demand is an industry pioneer and recognized innovator within the managed security industry and has been recognized throughout the years for its industry thought leadership, services innovation, and technology leadership. Our companyâ€™s mission is to relentlessly protect our clients against cyber-security threats with trailblazing technology and a thriving team to achieve operational excellence, trusted partnerships, and exceptional service. 
 Experience and Skills 
 An excellent background for this role would include moderate expertise in the areas of: 
 Knowledge of network security, information technology, and information systems 
 Owning projects throughout their lifecycle from installation and planning to execution, monitor/control through closing 
 Identifying and managing risk to set proper expectations and retain/improve customer satisfaction 
 Reporting on project updates and progress 
 Translating your knowledge of security services and products as business solutions to your customers to meet their needs 
 Providing timely issue resolution on security-related issues such as logging, reporting, alerting, and notifications 
 Effective communication and negotiation skills 
 Improving processes and procedures while focusing on improving the customer experience 
 Job Benefits 
 We offer opportunities for promotion, training, and a long-term career path for highly motivated individuals. For our regular employees we offer the following benefits: 
 Medical insurance HMO, PPO, and HDHP with HSA 
 Dental insurance HMO and PPO 
